FOCUSLAB

A simple interactive website about focus, productivity, and how people work bet.

I built this because I kept hearing "just focus" as advice, which isn't very helpful. So this project explores why focus is hard and gives a small tool to reflect on your own habits.

What it does:
- Explains the basics of focus and deep work
- Shows a few key stats about productivity
- Includes a Focus Analyzer where you can describe how you study and get feedback
- Have a dark mode toggle because light mode can get annoying

Tech Used:
- HTML
- CSS
- JavaScript (no frameworks)

Features:
- Smooth scrolling navigation
- Animated counters when the stats section appears
- Simple keyword-based analysis of study habits
- Responsive design

How to Run it:
1. Download or clone the repo
2. Open index.html in your browser

Why I made this:
I mostly made this site to practice front-end skills, but to also build something that can inform users about productivity and how you can't always "just focus".
Also I wanted to experiment with making projects feel more interactive instead of just static pages.

Future Improvements:
- images
- Add a pomodoro timer
- Store user results (localStorage or backend)
- make the analyzer smarter (right now it's basic)

Notes:
This isn't meant to be a complete productivity tool, it's just a small project that mixes design and interactivity.